The energy of one mole of photons is given by $E_{\mathrm{mole}} = E \times N_A$, where $N_A = 6.022 \times 10^{23} \mathrm{~mol}^{-1}$ is Avogadro's number. So, $E_{\mathrm{mole}} = (6.626 \times 10^{-19} \mathrm{~J}) \times (6.022 \times 10^{23} \mathrm{~mol}^{-1})$.

## Step 6: Perform the calculation for one mole of photons
$E_{\mathrm{mole}} = (6.626 \times 10^{-19} \mathrm{~J}) \times (6.022 \times 10^{23} \mathrm{~mol}^{-1}) = 3.991 \times 10^5 \mathrm{~J/mol} = 399.1 \mathrm{~kJ/mol}$.

