Solution: ## Step 1: Define the probability of drawing two balls of the same color from the two urns.
The probability of drawing two red balls is the product of the probability of drawing a red ball from the first urn and the probability of drawing a red ball from the second urn. The probability of drawing two blue balls is the product of the probability of drawing a blue ball from the first urn and the probability of drawing a blue ball from the second urn.

